Note: Although class II, use caution with beginners especially in cold temps. Cannot comment on<br/>
ranges between 800 and 1600-1700 cfs, but during our run at our higher level, current was swift and<br/>
almost constant. Our guy had several swims. The current made his swims long and gear retrieval<br/>
difficult. Had to hike him out with mild hypothermia setting in. Strainer in the current at S-turn<br/>
if the move across the waves is not made. </div>
