4-19-09 I went down the whitewater part of Elkhorn creek to find 3 helmets and 2 PFD's being<br/>
re-surfed in the dam , went further down the river to find 3 abandoned kayaks along the shore line.<br/>
Stooped in at canoe KY to report this and they were aware of a situation at the dam the previous<br/>
day in which a 16 year old girl was sucked back up to the dam in her kayak and flipped and was<br/>
re-surfed herself for several minutes until she flushed out and was washed up on the rock at the<br/>
start of the rapid and eventualy had to be rescued by the profesionals and taken to the hospital<br/>
for hyopothermmia. The moral of the story is please be carefull at the dam it is a dangerous<br/>
situation at any level. fortunatly this girl came out alright. </div>
